# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Please enter the commit message for your changes. Lines starting
# with '#' will be ignored, and an empty message aborts the commit.
#
# Type should be one of:
#   feat:     New features
#   fix:      Bug fixes
#   docs:     Documentation
#   style:    Code style/formatting
#   refactor: Code improvements
#   test:     Testing
#   chore:    Maintenance
#
# Scope examples: ui, api, core, auth, parser, agent, tool, cli
#
# Subject line:
#   - Use imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No dot (.) at the end
#   - Limit to 50 characters
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Use bullet points with - or *
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues: "Fixes #123", "References #456"
#   - Breaking changes: "Breaking: API endpoint changed"
#
# Examples:
#   feat(cli): add support for JSON output format
#   fix(agent): handle timeout errors gracefully
#   docs(readme): update installation instructions
#   refactor(core): simplify configuration loading
